bilingual.source: The agenda for the meeting is as follows.
Can you fwd me the meeting agenda?
bilingual.target: 你能转发会议议程给我吗？

bilingual.source: The agenda for the meeting is very brief.
The following is the agenda for the meeting.
This item is not on today's agenda.
bilingual.target: 这个项目不在今天的议程上。

bilingual.source: The itm on the agenda is very important.
bilingual.target: 议程上的项目非常重要。

bilingual.source: She always prepares the agenda well in advance.
bilingual.target: 她总是提前很久准备好议程。

bilingual.source: The new project is included in the meeting agenda.
bilingual.target: 会议议程中列入了新项目。

bilingual.source: Ere the meeting starts, review the agenda.
bilingual.target: 在会议开始之前，先审阅一下议程。

list.abstract: agenda（英 [əˈdʒendə]，美 [əˈdʒendə]），英语单词，作名词为议程；约会簿；日程表。例句：Playing cards was on the agenda, as well as learning to play mahjong (麻将).（扑克牌已列入日程，同时也要学习打麻将。）
这是一首Lupita D'Alessio演唱的歌曲。

yingyinNormal.en: Not if I get it on the agenda. No. Especially if you get it on the agenda.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除非我给提上议程。不，特别是你将它提上议程。

yingyinNormal.en: A suggested agenda, not a demand. We'll keep it mid-level. I won't get anywhere near it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 建议性议程，而不是命令，这件事由中层出面，我根本不插手。

yingyinNormal.en: We should limit the agenda to a couple of key issues: import tariffs on industrial manufactured goods, and export quotas on rare earth elements.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们得把议程限制在两个关键问题上，工业制品的进口关税, 以及稀土元素的出口限额。

yingyinNormal.en: I told him to bring up the agenda, suggest bullet points for the SED, but make no demands.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我让他提出议事日程，指出战略对话的关键点，但别提出要求。

yingyinNormal.en: He's hung up on the domestic agenda. Not a single word about China. His instincts are right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他被内政缠住了，对中国只字未提。他的直觉是对的。

yingyinNormal.en: That sounds like sarcasm, but I'm going to disregard it, because I have an agenda, paintball.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那听起来像讽刺啊，但是我决定无视它，因为我还有其他安排：玩彩弹枪。

yingyinNormal.en: It's clearly a setup. Someone's got a agenda. Dad, would you just shut up and listen to him? Nate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这明显是个陷阱，有人故意陷害我。爸，你能闭嘴听他说吗？内特。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you come down here with an agenda? No. I mean, I have been trying to reach Frank, but today was just…
yingyinNormal.zh: 你来这儿是有什么目的吗？没有，我，我一直想找弗兰克 但今天只是…

yingyinNormal.en: And for some reason, you don't want me to tell anyone. It is like everybody around here has got some kind of fucking agenda except for me. And, what?
yingyinNormal.zh: 不知道为什么，你不想让我告诉别人，好像除了我之外，这里所有人都在打着自己的小算盘，还有...怎么了？

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a plan of things to be done or problems to be addressed

examination_example.sentence: Such dimensions of reading suggest that we bring an implicit (often unacknowledged) <highlight>agenda</highlight> to any act of reading.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 阅读的这些层面表明，我们的任何阅读行为都带有一个暗含的（经常未被注意的）议程。

examination_example.sentence: First, most people do not realise that there are strong commercial <highlight>agendas</highlight> at work to keep them in passive consumption mode.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，大多数人没有意识到有强大的商业议程在起作用，使他们处于被动的消费模式。

word_usage.usage:
be on the agenda意为“例入会议议程的”，如：
Cutting the number of workers is not on the agenda.
削减工人人数并未例入会议议程。   
set the agenda意为“制定议程”，如：
He has set the agenda for future work in this field.
他已为今后这一领域的工作制定了议程。

examination_example.sentence: However, research <highlight>agendas</highlight> need to be focused on the needs of the poorest and most resource-limited countries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，研究议程需要集中于最贫穷和资源最有限的国家的需求。

examination_example.sentence: They came together to begin working out how to change research <highlight>agendas</highlight> to help meet the needs of farmers in poorer nations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们聚集在一起，开始研究如何改变研究议程，以帮助满足较贫穷国家农民的需求。
